The paper discusses the use of bibliometric data and complex-network theory to analyze the evolution of a scientific topic, which involves interdisciplinary and international effects. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Among these, cs.SI is the most likely category as it specifically deals with network analysis and visualization. The other categories are also relevant as they involve aspects of data analysis, information retrieval, and social implications of technology.
